definition.value: Mode of delivery in which there is causal influence from the intervention source to the recipient and from the recipient to the source.
Mode of delivery that involves delivery and receipt of the intervention or its components occurring at the same time or very close in time.
Mode of delivery that involves receipt of the intervention or its components taking place a significant period of time after delivery.
Mode of delivery that is not dependent on actions on the part of the intervention recipient.
Mode of delivery that requires some action on the part of the recipient.

Mode of delivery that involves application of typical elements of game playing  to other areas of activity, typically as an online marketing technique to encourage engagement with a product or service.
Includes point scoring, competition with others, and rules of play.
Mode of delivery that involves application of creativity on the part of the intervention recipient.
Includes art therapy, music therapy, dance and acting.
Individual human activity that enables a BCI to influence the outcome behaviour.
An aggregate of entities that form the environment in which a BCI is provided.
An intervention population who are exposed to a behaviour change intervention.
An intervention participant who is exposed to a behaviour change intervention.
"Exposed" encompasses both passive exposure to a behaviour change intervention e.g. nudges/environmental changes, and more active participation in a behaviour change intervention.
A personal attribute that is a time quality inhering in a person by virtue of how long since the person was born.
A personal attribute that is the pattern of a person's emotional, romantic and/or sexual attractions.
A sexual orientation of an individual who does not experience sexual attraction.
A sexual orientation of an individual who experiences sexual attraction to members of more than one sex.
A sexual orientation of an individual who experiences sexual attraction exclusively or primarily to members of a different sex.
A sexual orientation of an individual who experiences sexual attraction exclusively or primarily to members of the same sex.
A self-identity as being in the process of exploring one's sexual orientation.
A sexual orientation that is not exclusively homosexual or heterosexual, or of a person who does not identify with heterosexual, homosexual or bisexual labels.
A sexual orientation of an individual who is sure of their sexual orientation and reports it as other than asexual, bisexual, heterosexual, homosexual, queer or questioning.
A geographic location that is the country in which a person was born.
A person who has previously been a resident of a country and is now resident in another country.
A person who has at least one parent who is an immigrant.
A personal attribute that is belonging to a group that is characterised by the practice of a common religion by the group members.
presented in aggregated form as proportion/percentage belonging to a specified religious group
A linguistic capability that is realised by using a language accurately and appropriately in more than one setting.

label.value: ability to read in intervention language

definition.value: A linguistic capability that is realised by reading and understanding text in the intervention language.

label.value: ability to write in intervention language

definition.value: A linguistic capability that is realised by generating written text in the intervention language.

label.value: ability to speak in intervention language

definition.value: A linguistic capability that is realised by producing speech  in the intervention language.

label.value: ability to comprehend spoken intervention language

definition.value: A linguistic capability that is realised by following and understanding speech in the intervention language.

label.value: member of a one person household

definition.value: A person living alone in a household.
A person living in  a household with at least one other person.
A member of a multi-person household lives with at least one other person in the same dwelling.

label.value: member of a multi-person multi-generational household

definition.value: A member of a multi-person household where some household members belong to different generations.

A member of a multi-generational household lives with other people that are from more than one generation. A generation is all the people of about the same age within a society or within a particular family

label.value: member of a multi-person household all related

definition.value: A member of a multi-person household where all of the household members are related.

label.value: member of a multi-person household some related

definition.value: A member of a multi-person household where some household members are related.

label.value: member of a multi-person household not related

definition.value: A member of a multi-person household where none of the household members are related.
A personal attribute reflecting a benefit the person receives  derived from their capital or labour, usually measured in money.
An aggregate of the individual incomes received by all the members of a household.
An owner of a residential facility.
A person who lives in a residential facility of which they are the residential facility owner
A person who lives in a residential facility they do not own in return for paying an agreed sum of money to the residential facility owner

label.value: renter of housing from a social provider

definition.value: A renter who lives in a residential facility where the residential facility owner decides who can live in the residential facility based on their perceived social or economic needs.
A person who lives in a residential facility they do not own without paying an agreed sum of money to the residential facility owner.
A rent-free occupier who lives in the residential facility with the agreement of the residential facility owner.
A rent-free occupier who lives in the residential facility without the agreement of the residential facility owner.
A person who lives in a residential facility they do not own  with the agreement of the residential facility owner, by virtue of the occupier bearing a role realised in an employment process.
A person who does not own a residential facility and does not have an agreement with a residential facility owner that would enable them to live in a residential facility.
Individual income that an individual otherwise of low-income receives as a payment made by the state or an insurance scheme in the form of housing vouchers,  credit or benefits.

A policy holder role that inheres in a person who participates in the creation of an insurance contract designed to cover some or all of the cost of treating the insured person's illnesses or injuries as well as possibly providing preventive health care.
An object aggregate under the control of some person or organisation which confers an economic benefit to that person or organisation in an economic system.

label.value: quantity of valuable material resource owned

definition.value: A data item about the number of units of a valuable material resource possessed by a person.
